VERNACULAR NAME. — Citronelle (French) fide Papineau (in 
MacKee 37451
), but this name is given to several species of the genus with this odour (
Sarlin 1954
).

DISTRIBUTION. — The plant is known from Col d’Amieu (in the South) to Mandjélia (in the North), on the eastern part of the main Island “Grande Terre” (
Fig. 4
).

